<br>
You and I have been friends in game.  You left our guild shortly after I joined so there wasnt much time to get to know you. But from what time we spent I considered you a friend.  And still do.  However, when you left you disappeared off the face of Norrath.  Everyone thought you left the game or switched servers.  Hell, someone even said you sold your account and the Fermaga in game was a different person.<br>
<br>
I have seen you a couple of times recently.  And I felt bad when I couldnt help you on your shawl quest cause I was in the middle of POJ Trials.  If I had a little more notice I would have made a point to be there.<br>
<br>
I know a little, I think (tough without details) of what you are talking about.  I know some were very disappointed when you left (including me).  I know others were confused about why you left.  But myself and most others would still consider you a friend.  The guilt by association thing is crap and is there mostly in some because they are worried that the open style of the alliance is in jeopardy because of a few that would like to take it down and have tried to paralyze our channels and communication by passing out the passwords to those who like to screw with others.  I believe you guys refer to them as fucktards on this board and I think the name fits.  So those that leave without explanation are naturally held at a distance. Especially after Joannea/Karmianna/Fanfaire/Bitch and the continuing shit she pulls.<br>
<br>
Vazelle is a constantly changing place, both in the make up of guilds and the the things we do.  People screw over others on a daily basis.  It ALWAYS comes back to haunt them.  Guilds change. Just this weekend 3 guild leaders stepped down.  People change.  The only advice I can give is stick with your friends. and those that shit on you.  Ignore them.  <br>
<br>
